snippet.title: Ambers Closet - “There’s No Money In YouTube For LGBTQ Creators Anymore..”
snippet.description:
Class is in session! Ambers Closet stopped in and explained why she’s only making 6% of what she used to on YouTube, how the LGBTQ+ community are getting pushed out and what the “Adpocalypse” REALLY meant for creators. Enjoy

Subscribe Here! http://bit.ly/HeardWellSub
Check out our top videos! http://bit.ly/HeardWellTopVideos

About Heard Well:
Heard Well is the first music label entirely powered by social tastemakers and their communities. Heard Well partners with best in class influencers to curate playlists of their favorite emerging artists.

On this channel, we like to share our exclusive interviews with influencers like Tana Mongeau, Sam and Colby, and Connor Franta. Our How’d You Do It? Series is an intimate in-depth look into how some of the most popular influencers succeeded. Loud & Clear is a round table discussion with creatives who speak on topics that they are passionate about.
